The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Motilal Oswal IPO shines

 OUR CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, Aug. 20: The initial public offering of brokerage firm Motilal Oswal Financial Services Ltd got fully subscribed on its opening day today. The issue was subscribed 1.96 times and received 5,840,448 bids. 

 The company has allotted 2,982,710 equity shares at a face value of Rs 5, with a price band of Rs 725 to Rs 825. 

 The issue, which constitutes 10 per cent of the post-issue paid-up capital of the firm, will close on August 23. 

 The size of the offering is estimated at Rs 216.2 crore at the lower end and at Rs 246 crore at the upper end. 

 The financial services firm offers products and services such as retail wealth management, portfolio management services, institutional broking, venture capital management and investment banking services.

 The companys income from operations was Rs 358.75 crore during 2006-07 against Rs 257.65 crore in 2005-06. For the year ended March 31, the company recorded consolidated revenues and net profit of Rs 3,79.1 crore and Rs 69.58 crore respectively. 

 Motilal Oswal Financial Services operates through four subsidiaries Motilal Oswal Securities Ltd, Motilal Oswal Commodities Brokers Private Ltd, Motilal Oswal Venture Capital Advisors Private Ltd and Motilal Oswal Investment Advisors Private Ltd. 

 Motilal Oswal and Raamdeo Agrawal head the company, which was founded in 1987. The Mumbai-based firm has branches across 377 cities and towns. 

 Citigroup Global Markets India Pvt Ltd has been appointed the book running lead manager for the offering. 

 Last year, the company placed about 9.3 per cent equity for Rs 125 crore with New Vernon Private Equity Ltd and Bessemer Venture Partners.




